<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="445" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1785,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1786,1809]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[291,457,1785,1809]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Gorochovitettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[291,457,1785,1809]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">Gorochovitettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be rightly placed under the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[966,1111,1786,1809]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Metrodorinae">Metrodorinae</taxonomicName>
since it possesses the main diagnostic characters of the subfamily: pronotal lateral lobe that is directed outwards and obliquely truncated and with basitarsus and third segment of hind tarsus subequal in length (
<bibRefCitation author="Storozhenko" box="[821,1147,1856,1879]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" refString="Storozhenko, S. Y. &amp; Pushkar, T. I. (2015) A New Genus of Pygmy Locusts (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Metrodorinae) from Vietnam. Annales Zoologici (Warszawa), 65 (1), 65 - 69. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3161 / 00034541 ANZ 2015.65.1.006" type="journal article" year="2015">
Storozhenko &amp; Pushkar, 
<number box="[1089,1147,1856,1879]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="2015.0">2015</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is in spite of the fact that 
<taxonomicName box="[202,368,1889,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Gorochovitettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[202,368,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">Gorochovitettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also resembles representatives from the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[943,1085,1890,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cladonotinae">Cladonotinae</taxonomicName>
by frontal ridge (or scutellum) distinctively broader than scapus. Adding this genus to the current phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName box="[1040,1147,1925,1948]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tetrigidae</taxonomicName>
could help to confirm the subfamily status of this newly-erected genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
